====PayPal Mobile Plugin Installation Instructions====

1. If you haven't already been through and granted 'OnTechnology' access to set these permissions, you will need to login to your PayPal account and set the correct permissions
    - BMCreateButton
    - ....
    - ....

2. Unpack the contents of the plugin into your public directory. mobile.php will be in the base of your public directory, while the 'mobile' folder will be subfolder within that.

3. Merge mobile.htaccess file with your existing .htaccess file (if you already have one). This contains the mobile user agent string detection.

4. Check the site on your phone and test the transaction flow.